goals.question: What is the relationship between flight delay and distance?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'])
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distance')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    origin_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight origins?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Origin")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts()
    destinations = destination_counts.index
    counts = destination_counts.values

    plt.bar(destinations, counts)
    plt.xlabel('Destinations')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight destinations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(['Flights'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
